<% @page_title = 'Participant' %>
<div id="content">
 <h1>Discussion Group Participant Help Page</h1>
 <p>This page lists all of the <%= link_to "posts", general_help_path('discussions' 'posts') %> made by a given person to a <%= link_to "discussion group", general_help_path('discussions', 'groups') %>. The initial view is of all posts made within the past week, but there is a link to see older posts as well.</p>
 <p>The sidebar of the page lists the <%= link_to "forums", general_help_path('discussions', 'forums') %> in the discussion group that the person may <%= link_to "moderate", general_help_path('discussions', 'moderators') %>, with links to those forums. If you have created any forums, you can give moderatorship privileges for them on the participant page.</p>
 <p>The navigation bar for the page has a link to a <code>Members</code> page, which <%= link_to "lists every group participant", help_path('index') %>. </p>
 <h2>Post Format</h2>
 <p>Posts are displayed slightly differently on this page than when they are presented as part of a <%= link_to "topic thread", help_path('topics', 'show') %>.</p>
 <table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" class="posts wide beast">
 <tr class="post hentry">
  <td class="author vcard">
    <a href="#">Forum link</a> <span class='arrow'>&rarr;</span> <a href="#">Topic link</a><br/>
    <div class="date">
      <abbr class="updated" title="<%= Time.now.strftime("%b %d, %I:%M%p") %>">Post added <%= Date.today.strftime("%b %d, %Y") %></abbr>
    </div>
    <span class="edit"> 
      <a href="#">Edit Post</a>
    </span>
  </td>
  <td class="body entry-content"><p>Since the author of every post on this page is the same (the participant page looks at one person&#8217;s posts), there is no need to list the author with every post. Instead, links are provided to the topic and forum to which each post was added.</p></td>
 </tr>
</table> 
</div>
<div id="secondary">
 <h2>Related Topics</h2>
